    h1 Kitchen Sink

    .with-device(data-device-preview="/kitchen-sink/vue/dist/")
      p Framework7-Vue Kitchen Sink is a great place to get started, it has a lot of examples for all Framework7-Vue components and covers most of aspects.
      p It is recommended to use it as a reference during development.
      h2 Source Code
      p Vue Kitchen Sink source code is located at <a href="https://github.com/framework7io/framework7/tree/master/kitchen-sink/vue" target="_blank">GitHub repository</a>
      h2 Running Locally
      p To run Framework7-Vue Kitchen Sink locally we need:
      ol
        li
          p Download and unzip <a href="https://github.com/framework7io/framework7/" target="_blank">Framework7 GitHub repository</a> to a local folder
        li
          p Install <a href="http://nodejs.org/" target="_blank">Node.js</a> (if not installed)
        li
          p Install Gulp (if not installed) by executing the following command in terminal:
          :code
            npm install --global gulp
        li
          p Now, we need to install required dependencies. Go to the folder with downloaded and unzipped Framework7 repository and execute in terminal:
          :code
            npm install
        li
          p We are ready to launch Framework7-Vue Kitchen Sink, just execute in terminal:
          :code
            npm run vue






